        ArticleSeven:
          "ARTICLE 7: WHAT ARE YOUR RIGHTS? As a Person concerned by the Processing of Personal Data, you have various rights. However, these rights are not absolute and are subject to certain conditions, in accordance with the GDPR and other applicable texts in force, in particular Law no. 78-17 of 6 January 1978 known as 'Informatique et Libertés'. - 7.1 The right of access You have the right to obtain from PLANET EARTH NOW confirmation as to whether or not your personal data are or are not processed by the Association, as well as information on information on how it is processed. You also have the right to obtain a copy of your Personal Data processed by PLANET EARTH NOW. - 7.2 The right of rectification You may request PLANET EARTH NOW to take steps to correct your Personal Data if it is inaccurate or incomplete. - 7.3 The right to erasure ('right to be forgotten') You may request the erasure or deletion of your Personal Data. - 7.4 The right to limit processing You have the right to request the restriction of the Processing of Personal Data or to prevent further use of your Personal Data. Limiting the processing will not prevent the retention of your Personal Data, but PLANET EARTH will not be able to use them beyond the limits you wish to impose. - 7.5 The right to data portability You have the right to recover and re-use certain Personal Data concerning you if it is processed automatically by the Association. - 7.6 The right to object You have the right to object to certain types of processing, on grounds relating to your particular situation, at any time, insofar as such processing was carried out for the purposes of the legitimate interests pursued by PLANET EARTH NOW. - 7.7 The right to withdraw your consent  Where PLANET EARTH NOW processes your Personal Data on the lawful basis of your consent, you may withdraw your consent at any time. However, you are hereby informed that the withdrawal shall in no way affect the lawfulness of the processing which took place prior to the exercise of such right of withdrawal. - 7.8 The right to provide us with instructions on the use of your personal data after your death You have the right to provide PLANET EARTH NOW with instructions on the management (e.g. retention, erasure and disclosure) of your Personal Data after your death. You may change or revoke your instructions at any time. - 7.9 Right to lodge a complaint with the CNIL In the event that you are not satisfied with PLANET EARTH NOW's response to your complaint or if you believe that the Processing of your Personal Data does not comply with the applicable regulations on the protection of personal data, you may lodge a complaint with the competent data protection supervisory authority. The Commission Informatique et Libertés (CNIL) is the data protection authority in France.",
